# Books Catalog Database

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates a simple book catalog database using SQL Server.

The database stores information about books and their associated authors.

## Tables Included

### Authors
Stores author information.

### Books
Stores book details and links them to authors.

## SQL Concepts Used

- Table creation
- Primary key relationships
- Data insertion
- Datetime data types

## Example Use Cases

- Managing a digital book catalog
- Tracking authors and their books
- Library database design

## Tools Used

- Microsoft SQL Server
- SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)

## Purpose

This project demonstrates relational database design and basic data insertion operations using SQL.
